The Johannesburg Metro Police Department arrested three suspected Rolex Gang members in Fourways. JOHANNESBURG - Three suspects believed to be part of the "Rolex Gang" were arrested by Johannesburg Metro Police in Fourways. The suspects were arrested while following a potential victim. They were travelling in a red VW GTi and maroon Renault Sandero. "The suspects continued scouting Pineslopes Shopping Mall for a victim," read a statement by the JMPD. READ: Two more Rolex Gang members detained It went on to say that they spotted a potential victim who they followed driving towards William Nicol Drive. "The team managed to stop both vehicles and contain all occupants," said the JMPD. The arrests form part of a joint operation with the JMPD's K9 Unit, Hawks, Bad Boyz Security, SAPS and Tracker.